e engine oils, transmission oils, greases, automotive specialties, and industrial lubricants.Type of IndustryThe petroleum industry includes the global processes of exploration, extraction, refining, transporting (often by oil tankers and pipelines), and marketing petroleum products.Operational ProcessesSearching or exploring for underground or underwater oil and gas fields for drilling exploratoryDevelopment and production of crude oil or natural gasPetroleum distribution via affiliated retail outlets and natural gas distribution companies within the operationsMarket their products and services to their customersProductsThe company's profit margin ratio in five years are 3.26, 12.80, 2.89, 1.86, 1.84 respectively. It has increased from the 1st year to second year of 9.67% but decreased dramatically on succeeding years. The company have only a little portion of income return to them and the rest is paid for their expenses. The alarming decline of profitability ratios gives a big impact to the company. The rapid rise of petroleum products lessens the sales of the company. Thus, generate low income and profit margin.Profit Margin 2008   =     Net Income                                              Sales                                   =      150,288,738                                         4,615,216,959                                   =   3.26 %Profit Margin 2009    =     Net Income                                              Sales                                   =      751,476,659                                         5,873,051,463                                   =   12.80 %Profit Margin 2010    =     Net Income                                              Sales                                   =      427,213,509                                          14,792,188,213                                   =   2.89 %Profit Margin 2011    =     Net Income                                              Sales                                   =      510,500,835 